Uncertainty over the Greek political 
situation is sending shockwaves through global markets. HSBC's 
profit beat analysts expectations thanks to higher investment 
banking revenue in the U.S.. And Australia's Treasurer Wayne 
Swan says the country will return to a budget surplus by 2013. 
Bloomberg's Susan Li reports. (Source: Bloomberg)  Running Time: 01:10
 